## 8. Implementation Phases (Frontend Sprints)

### Phase A (Day 1–2): UI Skeleton + API wiring
- Layout dashboard
- Implement wallet connect + chain switch
- Implement /health check + show backend status

Deliverable: a working shell with connectivity

---

### Phase B (Day 3–5): Intent + Receipt UI
- Build Order Entry form
- Integrate /v1/intent/evaluate
- Show decision cards + reason codes
- Receipt viewer page

Deliverable: deterministic compliance demo works end-to-end (without Yellow matching)

---

### Phase C (Day 6–9): Session Key UI + Yellow hooks
- Create/select session key
- Display allowance + expiry countdown
- Add “session preflight” UI status

Deliverable: session keys are visible and govern user flow

---

### Phase D (Day 10–14): Matching + Escrow + Settlement visualization
- Submit order to state channel
- Display match events
- Display escrow lock and settlement tx

Deliverable: full lifecycle visible in UI (the judge moment)

---

### Phase E (Day 15+): Demo polish
- Demo Mode presets (Healthy / At-Risk / Fail)
- Event log panel
- Better error messaging
- Loading states and timeouts

Deliverable: reliable demo video ready

---

## 9. Acceptance Criteria (Frontend “Done” Definition)

Frontend is “done” for Yellow when:

- A new user can connect wallet in <10 seconds
- Session key creation/selection is visible and intuitive
- A PASS trade shows receipt + progresses to match/escrow/settlement
- A FAIL trade is blocked with a clear reason code
- At-risk conditions display amber warnings (but allow execution)
- The timeline always reflects state correctly
- Demo can be executed in 3 minutes without navigation errors

